strIntroduction: Discover Italica the first authentic Roman city in Spain located just 15 minutes from Sevilla. strIntroduction: Hop on a high-speed train and visit Luoyang an ancient city with history over thousands of years. Explore Long Men Grottoes one of the finest examples of Chinese Buddhist art. It houses tens of thousands of statues of Buddha and his disciples. Go to White Horse Temple the first Buddhist temple in China established in 68 AD under the patronage of Emperor Ming in Eastern Han Dynasty. It is considered by most believers as the cradle of Chinese Buddhism. Dont miss out on this tour!
strTitle: Luoyang One Day Excursion by High-Speed Train

strIntroduction: Experience the cultural night life of historical China with a Tang Dynasty Dancing show!
strTitle: Tang Dynasty Dancing Show in Xian - Private Half Night Tour

strIntroduction: Immerse yourself in Xians rich history and heritage on this magnificent tour to the Terracotta Warriors and Horses Museum. Then enjoy a customized city sightseeing tour and get to know more of this ancient capital of Shaanxi Province.
strTitle: Xian Terracotta Warriors and Horses Museum Private Tour with City Sightseeing

strIntroduction: Explore central Burma traveling from the Shan Plateau down to the Irrawaddy River. From the Shan lands enjoy the colonial charm of Kalaw then head down to Inle Lake and embark on a full day boat trip. Stop at the caves of Pindaya before heading down to Kiplings Mandalay the base for three nights as we cycle through the historic and picturesque surroundings. Cycle on by the former capital of an ancient kingdom before heading up to the magnificent heights of Mt. Popa down to the ancient city of Bagan before ending in Yangon with time for some shopping at the local market.
strTitle: Burma Adventure Cycling Tour - 14 Days

strIntroduction: Jump on the local commuter rail network and transit to explore beyond Yangon city center and into the neighborhoods not often seen by tourists!

strIntroduction: Immerse yourself in the culture and traditions of Yangon and find out why people from all over are flocking to Burma in this grassroots tour!

strIntroduction: Across the Yangon River the region of Twante is home to the Oh-Bo pottery community. Take a trip by local ferry and on foot to visit the artisans who create pottery using traditional methods and local materials. Feeling creative Dive in with a hands-on lesson literally and learn how its made. Finish it all off with lunch and a spectacular view from one of Myanmars highest pagodas.
strTitle: Hands-on Yangon - Small Group Tour

strIntroduction: Lose yourself in the bustle of Yangon as the city comes alive after sunset. Experience an evening the way locals do when night market stalls open and residents finish work and go to the streets. Shop eat and drink the evening away in the narrow alleyways. Taste a few local foods meet some local people and relax downtown with new friends and a cold beer at the end of the tour.
strTitle: Yangon Streets by Night - Small Group Tour

strIntroduction: In days past Zanzibar was known as a spice island exporting cloves vanilla nutmeg and cardamom across the world. The spices were brought over from Asia and South America and flourished in the tropical climes. Nowadays the plantations are a tribute to the islands past swapping spices for tourism combining both in a spice tour one of the most popular excursions on the island.
